EULOGY 03 | BLUE spent the night largely unbilled. The estate resents the missed opportunity.
EULOGY 04 | RED hoarded 36 pennies and spent it on nothing. The manor respects the discipline; the will does not reward it.
EULOGY 05 | And GOLD — who took from no one all night, and wept at no graves at all besides — was in the estate's estimation, almost kind.  How unusual.
EULOGY 06 | The estate adds, for the record: GOLD has been paid in blood money before. The ledger rounds up.
EULOGY 07 | The estate closes the ledger. Nothing is forgiven, but everything is filed, which the estate finds nearly the same.
